I have checked for interactions between buspirone and levothyroxine, specifically considering your age and Stage 3 Chronic Kidney Disease (CKD).

There is no known direct drug-drug interaction between buspirone and levothyroxine. However, because you have Stage 3 CKD, there is an important safety consideration regarding buspirone. Buspirone is metabolized by the liver and excreted by the kidneys; in patients with moderate renal impairment, the clearance of the drug can be reduced, which may lead to higher levels of the medication in your system. While it is not strictly prohibited (contraindicated), medical guidelines recommend using it with caution and potentially at lower doses in patients with kidney disease.

You should discuss your kidney function with your prescribing doctor to ensure the dose of buspirone is appropriate for your level of renal function.

