No, you should not use tetrahydrozoline (Visine) while taking phenelzine. This combination is considered contraindicated (severity level 5), meaning they should not be used together under any circumstances without direct medical supervision.

Phenelzine is a non-selective Monoamine Oxidase Inhibitor (MAOI). When combined with drugs like tetrahydrozoline, which can affect the reuptake of neurotransmitters, it can lead to a dangerous buildup of serotonin and norepinephrine in your system. This can result in a life-threatening hypertensive crisis (a sudden, severe spike in blood pressure) or serotonin syndrome.

Please consult your doctor or pharmacist for a safe alternative for eye redness.

