It is recommended that you do not take levothyroxine with your breakfast, especially if it includes milk or high-fiber cereal. These items can significantly reduce how much of the medication your body absorbs, making the treatment less effective.

According to the FDA, you should take levothyroxine on an empty stomach at least 30 to 60 minutes before eating breakfast or drinking anything other than water. This includes avoiding calcium-rich foods like milk and high-fiber foods at the same time as your dose.

