Based on your genetic test results and clinical guidelines, your status as a CYP2D6 poor metabolizer is significant regarding paroxetine hydrochloride. 

Individuals who are CYP2D6 poor metabolizers tend to have 2 to 5 times higher levels of paroxetine in their system compared to normal metabolizers. This increased exposure can increase the risk of side effects. According to CPIC guidelines, it is often recommended to consider starting at half the standard dose and titrating slowly to monitor for tolerance, or to consider alternative medications that are not as heavily dependent on the CYP2D6 pathway.

You should discuss these results with your prescribing physician before starting the medication. They may need to adjust your starting dose or select a different therapy based on this pharmacogenomic information.

