Combining rasagiline and dopamine is considered high-risk. Rasagiline is a Monoamine Oxidase Inhibitor (MAOI), and dopamine is a sympathomimetic medication. When taken together, they can cause a dangerous and potentially life-threatening spike in blood pressure known as a hypertensive crisis. 

Since you also have COPD, any severe cardiovascular reaction like a hypertensive crisis could be even more complicated to manage. You should not start rasagiline without discussing this specific combination with your healthcare provider immediately.

