I have found a critical safety concern regarding the combination of phenelzine and desipramine. 

Taking these two medications together is generally contraindicated (meaning they should not be used together) because they belong to drug classes that interact severely. Phenelzine is a non-selective monoamine oxidase inhibitor (MAOI), and desipramine is a tricyclic antidepressant (a non-selective monoamine reuptake inhibitor). 

Combining these can lead to a dangerous excess of serotonin and norepinephrine in your system, potentially causing a life-threatening condition called serotonin syndrome or a sudden, severe increase in blood pressure (hypertensive crisis). 

**You must consult your doctor before taking these together. They will likely need to manage a supervised "washout" period if you are switching from one to the other.**

