Based on your genetic test result indicating SLCO1B1 poor function, there is a significant safety concern regarding the use of simvastatin. 

Individuals with this genetic profile have a reduced ability to transport simvastatin into the liver, leading to higher levels of the medication in the bloodstream. This significantly increases the risk of myopathy (muscle pain or weakness), especially at standard or higher doses. According to clinical guidelines, it is recommended to either use a much lower dose of simvastatin or, more commonly, switch to an alternative statin like pravastatin or rosuvastatin which are less affected by this specific gene.

You should contact your prescribing doctor immediately to discuss these results before starting the medication. They will need to adjust your prescription to a safer alternative.

