Based on the medical records, there is a significant safety concern regarding the use of rivaroxaban (Xarelto) and phenytoin (Dilantin) together. Phenytoin is a strong inducer of the enzymes (CYP3A4) and transport systems (P-gp) that your body uses to process rivaroxaban. When taken together, phenytoin can significantly lower the levels of rivaroxaban in your blood, making the anticoagulant much less effective and increasing your risk of blood clots.

You should consult your healthcare provider immediately before taking these medications together. They may need to adjust your seizure medication or choose a different anticoagulant that does not interact with phenytoin. Regarding your asthma, no direct contraindications were found with these specific medications at your age.

