You should avoid consuming dairy products like milk or yogurt at the same time as your doxycycline monohydrate dose. 

Calcium found in dairy products can bind (chelate) to the medication in your digestive tract, which reduces how much of the antibiotic your body absorbs by about 20% to 30%. This could make the treatment less effective at fighting your infection. To ensure the medicine works correctly, you should separate your dose from any dairy products, antacids, iron, or calcium supplements by at least 2 hours.

